arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingMIB.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingMIB
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingMIB.contactinfo: Hewlett Packard Company 8000 Foothills Blvd. Roseville, CA 95747
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingMIB.description: This MIB module contains HPE proprietary mib definitions for managing MGMD Snooping services.

MgmdSnoopingGroupTypeDefinition.name: MgmdSnoopingGroupTypeDefinition
MgmdSnoopingGroupTypeDefinition.description: This type distinguishes the different ways of tracking groups on this device having multicast joins. The method of tracking is primarily determined by the MGMD Snooping feature configuration. In particular if the snooping feature is enabled then port level tracking is the default, which results in Filtered groups. When users create static groups these groups will be categorized as static and groups will exist till user unconfigure them.

MgmdSnoopingConfigPortModeType.name: MgmdSnoopingConfigPortModeType
MgmdSnoopingConfigPortModeType.description: Mode in auto means MGMD Snooping will be working as per specs on these ports that is when a join comes for a group on this port data packets sent to that group will be forwarded on that port. Blocked means all outgoing data packets and incoming joins will be blocked on that port.Forward means all the packets irrespective of whether the join is received for a group or not packets will be sent or received on these ports in other wording forwarded ports acts like router detected ports.

arubaWiredMgmdIgmpSnoopingControlDropUnk.name: arubaWiredMgmdIgmpSnoopingControlDropUnknownMulticast
arubaWiredMgmdIgmpSnoopingControlDropUnk.description: When enabled along with IGMP Snooping, any IP Multicast packets that are not joined by an IGMP host will be restricted to ports that have detected a multicast router or ports that are configured to always forward IP multicast. When set to disabled or when IGMP Snooping is disabled, the unjoined IP multicast packets will be flooded out all ports in the VLAN. Permanently assigned multicast addresses are always flooded and so are not impacted by this object.

arubaWiredMgmdIgmpSnoopingEnabledVLANCou.name: arubaWiredMgmdIgmpSnoopingEnabledVLANCount
arubaWiredMgmdIgmpSnoopingEnabledVLANCou.description: Current total count of VLANs with IGMP Snooping enabled.

arubaWiredMgmdIgmpSnoopingMcastGroupJoin.name: arubaWiredMgmdIgmpSnoopingMcastGroupJoinsCount
arubaWiredMgmdIgmpSnoopingMcastGroupJoin.description: Current total count of Multicast groups joined.

arubaWiredMgmdIgmpSnoopingMcastFilteredG.name: arubaWiredMgmdIgmpSnoopingMcastFilteredGroupJoinsCount
arubaWiredMgmdIgmpSnoopingMcastFilteredG.description: Current total count of groups being traced across all VLANs on a per port basis. Traffic for these groups will be filtered to flow only to ports with active joins, subject to hardware resource limitations such as the maximum number of groups supported by the hardware.

arubaWiredMgmdIgmpSnoopingMcastExcludeGr.name: arubaWiredMgmdIgmpSnoopingMcastExcludeGroupJoinsCount
arubaWiredMgmdIgmpSnoopingMcastExcludeGr.description: Number of multicast groups in the EXCLUDE mode.

arubaWiredMgmdIgmpSnoopingMcastIncludeGr.name: arubaWiredMgmdIgmpSnoopingMcastIncludeGroupJoinsCount
arubaWiredMgmdIgmpSnoopingMcastIncludeGr.description: Number of multicast groups in the INCLUDE mode.

arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingControlDropUnkn.name: arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingControlDropUnknownMulticast
arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingControlDropUnkn.description: When enabled along with MLD Snooping, any IPv6 Multicast packets that are not joined by an MLD host will be restricted to ports that have detected a multicast router or ports that are configured to always forward IPv6 multicast. When set to disabled or when MLD Snooping is disabled, the unjoined IPv6 multicast packets will be flooded out all ports in the VLAN. Permanently assigned multicast addresses are always flooded and so are not impacted by this object.

arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingEnabledVLANCoun.name: arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingEnabledVLANCount
arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingEnabledVLANCoun.description: Current total count of VLANs with MLD Snooping enabled.

arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingMcastGroupJoins.name: arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingMcastGroupJoinsCount
arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingMcastGroupJoins.description: Current total count of Multicast groups joined.

arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingMcastExcludeGro.name: arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingMcastExcludeGroupJoinsCount
arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingMcastExcludeGro.description: Number of multicast groups in EXCLUDE mode.

arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingMcastIncludeGro.name: arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingMcastIncludeGroupJoinsCount
arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingMcastIncludeGro.description: Number of multicast groups in INCLUDE mode.

arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingMcastFilteredGr.name: arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingMcastFilteredGroupJoinsCount
arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingMcastFilteredGr.description: Current total count of groups being traced across all VLANs on a per port basis. Traffic for these groups will be filtered to flow only to ports with active joins, subject to hardware resource limitations such as the maximum number of groups supported by the hardware.

arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingSendRouterAlert.name: arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingSendRouterAlertPaddingOption
arubaWiredMgmdMldSnoopingSendRouterAlert.description: This enumerated value indicates whether the router alert option has to include padding after option type (1), include padding before option type (2) or should not be sent(3).

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanTable.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanTable
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanTable.description: This table object contains the MGMD Snooping VLAN information.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryVid.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryVid
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryVid.description: The vid value of the VLAN for which MGMD Snooping is enabled. The table is indexed by the vid value and the InetAddressType to allow for VLANs that may be configured in both IPv4 and IPv6 modes.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryType.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryType
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryType.description: The address type of this VLAN. This entry along with the vid value acts as the index to the mgmdSnoopingVlanTable. A VLAN may be configured in multiple modes concurrently, e.g., in IPv4 and IPv6 modes connected to the same VLAN; however, the traffic is considered to be logically separate.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntrySnoopingF.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntrySnoopingFeature
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntrySnoopingF.description: Turns MGMD Snooping feature on and off.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryControlDr.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryControlDropUnknownMulticastStatus
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryControlDr.description: The operational status of the MGMD Snooping Control Unknown Multicast mode. A value of true indicates the mgmdSnoopingVlanEntryControlDropUnknownMulticastStatus setting is operational. A value of false indicates the mgmdSnoopingVlanEntryControlDropUnknownMulticastStatus setting is not operational.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryQuerierPo.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryQuerierPort
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryQuerierPo.description: Logical port which the querier is connected to. This is determined by the presence of querier packets on this port.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryFilteredJ.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryFilteredJoins
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryFilteredJ.description: Current total count of groups on this VLAN being tracked on a per port basis. Traffic for these groups will be filtered to flow only to ports with active joins, subject to hardware resource limitations such as the maximum number of groups supported by the hardware.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryPortsWith.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryPortsWithMcastRouter
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryPortsWith.description: List of multicast router detected ports on this VLAN.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryStatJoinT.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryStatJoinTimeouts
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryStatJoinT.description: Number of times joins got timed out on this VLAN.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryStaticJoi.description: Total count of user created static groups on this VLAN.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryOtherQuer.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryOtherQuerierInterval
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryOtherQuer.description: The length of time that must pass before a multicast router decides that there is no longer another multicast router which should be the querier. This value MUST be ((the Robustness Variable) times (the Query Interval)) plus (one half of one Query Response Interval).

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryOtherQuer.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryOtherQuerierExpiryTime
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryOtherQuer.description: The minimum amount of time remaining before a multicast router decides that there is no longer another multicast router which should be the querier.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryOtherQuer.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryOtherQuerierRobustness
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingVlanEntryOtherQuer.description: The Robustness Variable allows tuning for the expected packet loss on a subnet. If a subnet is expected to be lossy, the Robustness Variable may be increased. MGMD is robust to (Robustness Variable-1) packet losses.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheVid.description: The VLAN for which this entry contains information for an IP multicast group address.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheAddress.description: The IP multicast group address for which this entry contains information.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheSelf.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheSelf
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheSelf.description: An indication of whether the local system is a member of this group address on this VLAN.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheLastReporter.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheLastReporter
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheLastReporter.description: The IP address of the source of the last membership report received for this IP Multicast group address on this VLAN. If no membership report has been received, this object has the value 0.0.0.0. or 0::0

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheUpTime.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheUpTime
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheUpTime.description: The time elapsed since this entry was created.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheExpiryTime.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheExpiryTime
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheExpiryTime.description: The minimum amount of time remaining before this entry will be aged out. A value of 0 indicates that the entry is only present because arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheSelf is true and that if the router left the group, this entry would be aged out immediately. Note that some implementations may process Membership Reports from the local system in the same way as reports from other hosts, so a value of 0 is not required.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheGroupType.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheGroupType
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheGroupType.description: Reference MgmdSnoopingGroupTypeDefinition will indicate the type of group.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheJoinedPorts.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheJoinedPorts
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheJoinedPorts.description: Logical ports with active MGMD joins on them for this entry. For Filtered groups this will be the logical ports which have active joins. For static groups this will include all logical ports on the VLAN running MGMD Snooping.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheStatus.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheStatus
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheStatus.description: The status of this row, by which new entries may be created, or existing entries deleted from this table.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheJoinsRcvd.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheJoinsRcvd
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheJoinsRcvd.description: This represents the number of MGMD Reports received for this group.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheFilterMode.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheFilterMode
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheFilterMode.description: The value indicates whether the group state is the INCLUDE(1)/ EXCLUDE(2).

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheVersion1HostT.description: The time remaining after which the local router will assume that there are no longer any MGMD version 1 members on the IP subnet attached to this VLAN.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheVersion2HostT.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheVersion2HostTimer
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingCacheVersion2HostT.description: The time remaining after which the local router will assume that there are no longer any MGMD version 2 members on the IP subnet attached to this VLAN.

arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingPortConfigEntryPor.name: arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingPortConfigEntryPortModeFeature
arubaWiredMgmdSnoopingPortConfigEntryPor.description: The operational status of the MGMD Snooping feature for this port or trunk. 1 implies that all IP Multicast traffic will be monitored on the port, 2 implies that IP Multicast traffic will be dropped on the port, and 3 implies that all IP Multicast traffic will be forwarded without the switch examining it.
